Our wildlife sanctuary also doubles as an endangered species reintroduction platform to translocate animals to parts of its natural range where populations have significantly declined or been lost. Aiming to establish a viable population within translocated areas. Our most recent animals for release are our lions. Brought to us from other zoos due to being rejected by their mother at a very young age. Upon arrival these animals were in poor condition, we have trained them and nursed them back to health.
